&lt;concerning the Sun gateway having 2 machine names&gt;

RFCs notwithstanding, SunOS requires that a Sun with 2 network interfaces
have a unique name for each of the network interfaces. In Sun-land, you are
not really naming the _host_, but the _network interface_, hence ie0 gets
one name and ie1 gets another.

If the Sun is an ND server, then (optimally) the ND clients should be on
its ie0 side, and should think of their ND server as its ie0 name.

The network interface connected to the ARPAnet should be named what the
ARPAnet calls your machine.

You can also alias machine names in the /etc/hosts file, but don't alias 1
name to both of the interfaces.

Hope this helps,

..Celeste Stokely
